WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
STAR TREK

2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
STRANGE

3
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
NEW

4
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
WＯRLDS

5
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
SEASON 01  #  EPISODE 04
"Momento Mori"

6
00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:27.680
<i>Previously. on </i>STAR TREK STRANGE NEW WORLDS<i>...</i>

7
00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.420
Lieutenant La'An Noonien-Singh. Chief of Security.

8
00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:32.490
I've been assigned as acting 1ˢᵗ Officer.

9
00:00:32.490 --> 00:00:33.620
No sedatives.

10
00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:35.120
CHAPEL: Maybe I wasn't clear about...

11
00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:36.410
the terrible pain part.

12
00:00:36.410 --> 00:00:38.540
Maybe I wasn't clear when I said no.

13
00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:40.710
The Gorn captured my family's colony ship.

14
00:00:40.710 --> 00:00:42.880
I was the only one to survive.

15
00:00:43.540 --> 00:00:44.710
Can I help?

16
00:00:46.670 --> 00:00:47.760
No.

17
00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:50.380
SPOCK: <i>Hemmer may not be able to see. but his other senses compensate.</i>

18
00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:52.470
HEMMER: <i>Compensate? They are superior.</i>

19
00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:54.510
What the... How did you...

20
00:00:54.510 --> 00:00:56.310
PIKE: <i>You beat out. how many...</i>

21
00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:58.600
a 1.000 applicants?
- Several 1.000.

22
00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:02.020
Both my parents were killed in a shuttle accident.

23
00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:04.690
<i>Didn't feel like I fit anywhere.</i>

24
00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:07.530
I understand you did not come to Starfleet the way many of us have.

25
00:01:07.530 --> 00:01:09.240
That you are not sure you wish to stay.

26
00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:12.070
Starfleet would be fortunate to have an Officer like you.

27
00:01:21.830 --> 00:01:25.750
LA'AN: <i>Security Officer's Log. Stardate 3177.3.</i>

28
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:28.590
<i>The</i> Enterprise <i>is currently en route to deliver...</i>

29
00:01:28.590 --> 00:01:32.180
<i>an atmospheric processor upgrade to Finibus III.</i>

30
00:01:32.180 --> 00:01:35.050
<i>Without our assistance. the air on this remote colony...</i>

31
00:01:35.050 --> 00:01:37.220
<i>will become unbreathable in a matter of weeks.</i>

32
00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:39.560
<i>As we prepare for our arrival...</i>

33
00:01:39.560 --> 00:01:42.190
<i>we pause to honor Starfleet Remembrance Day.</i>

34
00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:47.150
[PUBLIC ADDRESS SYSTEM CHIMES]

35
00:01:47.290 --> 00:01:49.210
PIKE: <i>Attention. this is the Captain speaking.</i>

36
00:01:50.150 --> 00:01:51.610
<i>Many of us have known those...</i>

37
00:01:51.610 --> 00:01:53.200
<i>who have made the ultimate sacrifice.</i>

38
00:01:53.990 --> 00:01:56.600
♪♪

39
00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.760
<i>Officers. scientists...</i>

40
00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:01.410
<i>civilians who gave their lives...</i>

41
00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:03.250
<i>in the hope for galactic peace.</i>

42
00:02:03.250 --> 00:02:06.840
<i>Today we remember the friends and comrades we lost.</i>

43
00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:10.130
<i>Exploration can exact a heavy toll.</i>

44
00:02:11.050 --> 00:02:13.630
<i>As Captain. there is no loss more devastating...</i>

45
00:02:13.640 --> 00:02:15.300
<i>than that of a crew member.</i>

46
00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:17.470
<i>Remembrance Day is about them.</i>

47
00:02:18.470 --> 00:02:20.560
<i>Those of us left behind wear the insignia...</i>

48
00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:22.600
<i>of past ships on which we served together.</i>

49
00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:25.270
As we honor the lives that have been given...

50
00:02:26.150 --> 00:02:29.110
let us also be grateful to be still on the journey.

51
00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:31.820
HEMMER: Tell me...

52
00:02:31.820 --> 00:02:34.950
what is the essential function of the AP 350 device?

53
00:02:35.660 --> 00:02:37.200
It's an air filter.

54
00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:39.330
Cadets.

55
00:02:39.870 --> 00:02:42.580
Never read the assignment materials in advance.

56
00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:46.290
Invented by a Zigwel Orgon in 2234.

57
00:02:46.290 --> 00:02:49.300
1ˢᵗ deployed on <i>Titan</i> after the Crestbrock mining collapse.

58
00:02:49.300 --> 00:02:52.010
Unlike its predecessors. the upgraded model. AP 350...

59
00:02:52.010 --> 00:02:55.340
uses charged positron rods to stabilize the ion matrix...

60
00:02:55.340 --> 00:02:58.680
which. then. well. filters the air.

61
00:03:00.680 --> 00:03:01.980
Fine.

62
00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:04.350
Points granted.

63
00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:07.690
[MALE VOICE OVER P.A.] <i>Lieutenant Taft. please report to the shuttle bay.</i>

64
00:03:07.690 --> 00:03:11.530
Most cadets labor their rotation through engineering...

65
00:03:11.530 --> 00:03:12.900
dreaming of Command.

66
00:03:12.910 --> 00:03:15.530
UHURA: I'm enjoying it here. actually.

67
00:03:15.530 --> 00:03:17.410
Engineering is a lot like linguistics.

68
00:03:18.040 --> 00:03:19.160
Is that so?

69
00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:21.830
Sure. Both are dependent on...

70
00:03:21.830 --> 00:03:23.920
how seemingly unrelated systems communicate.

71
00:03:25.170 --> 00:03:26.340
Big ideas.

72
00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:28.840
To impress me...

73
00:03:28.840 --> 00:03:31.380
you're going to need to do better than theorize.

74
00:03:32.720 --> 00:03:34.050
Challenge accepted.

75
00:03:39.970 --> 00:03:41.430
You're not wearing your pin.

76
00:03:41.430 --> 00:03:43.270
No big deal.
- Okay.

77
00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:46.230
You know how I feel about it.
- Yeah. I definitely do.

78
00:03:46.230 --> 00:03:48.360
The past is the past. there's no point in looking back.

79
00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:49.440
Closure seems like a reason...

80
00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:51.280
Una. stop.
- Starfleet has resources...

81
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:53.240
I am not going to let some Doctor inside my head...

82
00:03:53.240 --> 00:03:55.030
to try and fix me. I'm not broken. I'm fine.

83
00:03:58.080 --> 00:04:00.250
Captain. we've arrived in orbit.

84
00:04:03.370 --> 00:04:06.080
PIKE: So. where's the welcome wagon?

85
00:04:07.500 --> 00:04:10.340
Sir. Finibus III is still not responding to any hails.

86
00:04:10.340 --> 00:04:12.170
When was their last transmission?

87
00:04:12.170 --> 00:04:14.930
According to the log. 2 days ago.

88
00:04:14.930 --> 00:04:17.010
I have been monitoring radio wave interference...

89
00:04:17.010 --> 00:04:19.510
emanating from a large brown dwarf in close proximity.

90
00:04:19.510 --> 00:04:21.180
That's what's jamming the signal?

91
00:04:21.180 --> 00:04:22.930
Possible. Let me adjust sensors.

92
00:04:24.520 --> 00:04:25.690
[BEEPING]

93
00:04:25.690 --> 00:04:28.150
The brown dwarf does not appear to be the problem. Captain.

94
00:04:28.940 --> 00:04:30.400
Finibus III is not responding...

95
00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:33.110
because the colony's communications satellite has been destroyed.

96
00:04:36.870 --> 00:04:37.870
Accidental?

97
00:04:38.410 --> 00:04:39.830
Impossible to say. Captain.

98
00:04:41.370 --> 00:04:42.620
All right.

99
00:04:42.620 --> 00:04:43.910
Report it to Starfleet.

100
00:04:44.670 --> 00:04:47.290
Protocol now is we investigate. make contact on the ground.

101
00:04:47.290 --> 00:04:50.420
Go slow. No assumptions until we gather more intel.

102
00:04:51.960 --> 00:04:53.300
I'll prep a landing party.

103
00:04:53.720 --> 00:04:55.300
Lieutenant Noonien-Singh.

104
00:05:02.520 --> 00:05:03.850
[SOFT WARBLING]

105
00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:07.730
UNA: There are supposed to be 100s of people here.

106
00:05:08.440 --> 00:05:10.160
TODD: I'm not getting any human life signs.

107
00:05:10.690 --> 00:05:12.110
UNA: Rushed evacuation?

108
00:05:12.690 --> 00:05:15.450
LA'AN: Rushed under fire. Those are blast marks.

109
00:05:16.030 --> 00:05:17.820
Definitely a skirmish here.

110
00:05:19.490 --> 00:05:21.160
[METAL RATTLING]

111
00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:46.900
[BARKING]
- [GASPS]

112
00:05:48.230 --> 00:05:50.730
[SIGHS]
- [OTHERS LAUGHING]

113
00:05:52.110 --> 00:05:53.280
That's not funny.

114
00:06:02.450 --> 00:06:04.710
Commander. come take a look.

115
00:06:10.210 --> 00:06:11.550
UNA: Not an evacuation.

116
00:06:12.380 --> 00:06:13.550
A massacre.

117
00:06:14.670 --> 00:06:16.710
LA'AN: Looks like the bodies were all dragged here.

118
00:06:18.050 --> 00:06:19.390
But where are they now?

119
00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:22.470
[BEEPING]

120
00:06:26.060 --> 00:06:29.270
Number One. we've got an unidentified ship up here.

121
00:06:29.270 --> 00:06:30.560
We're beaming you back up.

122
00:06:32.530 --> 00:06:34.280
The Away Team is on board. Captain.

123
00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:37.240
No Federation badges. Ship has her shields up.

124
00:06:37.910 --> 00:06:40.490
Scans reveal multiple life forms. Unable to identify.

125
00:06:40.490 --> 00:06:42.370
Hail them. All channels.
- [SYSTEM WARBLING]

126
00:06:42.370 --> 00:06:43.580
No response.

127
00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:45.000
Yellow alert. Shields up.

128
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:46.250
Captain. they're hailing us.

129
00:06:46.250 --> 00:06:47.920
[SYSTEM CHIMING]

130
00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:49.170
Belay that order.

131
00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:51.460
On screen.

132
00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:54.130
[EXHALES]

133
00:06:54.130 --> 00:06:56.340
<i>Thank God. You're Starfleet.</i>

134
00:06:56.970 --> 00:06:59.970
This is Captain Christopher Pike of the <i>U.S.S. Enterprise.</i> And you are?

135
00:06:59.970 --> 00:07:02.600
<i>Professor Thandie of Finibus III.</i>

136
00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:05.930
<i>My apologies. but I needed to be sure.</i>

137
00:07:05.930 --> 00:07:08.270
What's your status?
<i>- Most of us are injured.</i>

138
00:07:08.730 --> 00:07:12.520
<i>This is a cargo vessel. Life support is overextended.</i>

139
00:07:12.520 --> 00:07:14.190
Prepare for transport to the <i>Enterprise.</i>

140
00:07:14.190 --> 00:07:17.610
<i>Uh. Captain. this ship is used for hauling radioactive ore.</i>

141
00:07:17.610 --> 00:07:19.200
<i>The hull is transport resistant.</i>

142
00:07:19.200 --> 00:07:23.120
Zuniga. attach a deep space transport tube.

143
00:07:23.120 --> 00:07:25.000
[BEEPING]
- Can you tell me what happened?

144
00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:27.790
<i>A blast from the sky took out our main colony structure.</i>

145
00:07:28.540 --> 00:07:30.670
<i>We then all heard a loud ringing sound.</i>

146
00:07:32.300 --> 00:07:34.800
<i>Everything gets blurry after that.</i>

147
00:07:37.880 --> 00:07:40.800
No signs of any other vessels. No residual warp signatures.

148
00:07:44.680 --> 00:07:45.730
Hang on.

149
00:07:46.310 --> 00:07:48.100
Everything's going to be all right.

150
00:07:57.860 --> 00:07:59.860
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

151
00:08:01.620 --> 00:08:03.620
[WOMAN SOBBING]
- [COUGHING]

152
00:08:07.370 --> 00:08:09.000
I can't thank you enough.

153
00:08:09.630 --> 00:08:12.000
All of us owe you our lives.

154
00:08:12.590 --> 00:08:14.630
UNA: We're still trying to figure out who did this.

155
00:08:14.840 --> 00:08:16.510
Did anyone see anything?

156
00:08:16.510 --> 00:08:18.470
A farmer saw streaks in the sky.

157
00:08:19.180 --> 00:08:22.430
He said it was like rain on fire.

158
00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:27.980
Most of us were unconscious by then.

159
00:08:27.980 --> 00:08:30.350
LA'AN: We count about a 100 with you.

160
00:08:30.350 --> 00:08:32.270
What happened to the rest of the colony?

161
00:08:32.270 --> 00:08:33.360
I don't know.

162
00:08:33.360 --> 00:08:35.980
We woke up and they were gone.

163
00:08:35.980 --> 00:08:38.860
No bodies. Just blood.

164
00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:47.200
Ringing... Maybe an ultrasonic cannon?

165
00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:48.710
Rain on fire.

166
00:08:48.710 --> 00:08:51.000
Sub-orbital plasma bombardment.

167
00:08:51.630 --> 00:08:53.040
No ships on our sensors...

168
00:08:53.040 --> 00:08:54.840
but my gut is telling me something's off.

169
00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:57.210
Fig! Come here. stop! Fig!
- Hey. hey. hey.

170
00:08:57.220 --> 00:08:58.880
The monsters are coming. hide!

171
00:08:58.880 --> 00:09:01.390
Honey. you know monsters aren't real.

172
00:09:02.720 --> 00:09:03.890
What monsters?

173
00:09:04.260 --> 00:09:05.890
The ones who took Daddy.

174
00:09:06.810 --> 00:09:08.350
This has been awful for her.

175
00:09:11.150 --> 00:09:12.730
Did you see something. Fig?

176
00:09:16.230 --> 00:09:18.190
It was dark. I didn't see it.

177
00:09:18.780 --> 00:09:21.200
But it makes noises. Like this.

178
00:09:21.660 --> 00:09:24.330
[CLUCKING TONGUE]

179
00:09:32.290 --> 00:09:33.880
La'An to Bridge.

180
00:09:33.880 --> 00:09:36.840
<i>We need to scan the area for polarized EM signatures.</i>

181
00:09:36.840 --> 00:09:37.840
<i>Quickly.</i>

182
00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:41.430
What is it?

183
00:09:42.010 --> 00:09:43.140
I'm not sure yet.

184
00:09:46.600 --> 00:09:48.980
Sensors are detecting a slight optical distortion...

185
00:09:48.980 --> 00:09:50.940
near the 2ⁿᵈ moon. A hologram. sir.

186
00:09:51.940 --> 00:09:53.610
Raise shields! Now!

187
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:55.650
Raise shields. Red alert.
- ORTEGAS: We can't.

188
00:09:55.650 --> 00:09:57.780
The transport tube. We can't raise shields.

189
00:09:57.780 --> 00:09:59.780
[ALARM BLARING]

190
00:10:00.650 --> 00:10:01.780
Oh. no.

191
00:10:10.580 --> 00:10:11.790
La'An. move.

192
00:10:13.460 --> 00:10:14.790
It's the Gorn.

193
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:43.430
STAR TREK

194
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:43.430
STRANGE

195
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:43.430
NEW

196
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:43.430
WＯRLDS

197
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:43.430
SEASON 01  #  EPISODE 04
"Momento Mori"

198
00:10:35.610 --> 00:10:36.900
PIKE: Space.

199
00:10:38.610 --> 00:10:40.110
The final frontier.

200
00:10:42.910 --> 00:10:46.030
These are the voyages of the starship Enterprise.

201
00:10:47.990 --> 00:10:49.660
Its 5-year mission...

202
00:10:50.660 --> 00:10:52.750
to explore strange new worlds...

203
00:10:55.420 --> 00:10:56.880
to seek out new life...

204
00:10:58.510 --> 00:11:00.300
and new civilizations...

205
00:11:01.920 --> 00:11:03.530
to boldly go...

206
00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:05.590
where no one has gone before.

207
00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:08.100
[ ♪ THEME MUSIC ♪ ]

208
00:11:10.900 --> 00:11:12.900
♪♪

209
00:11:38.260 --> 00:11:40.310
♪♪

210
00:12:06.290 --> 00:12:08.330
♪♪

211
00:12:26.260 --> 00:12:28.260
[ALARM BLARING]

212
00:12:30.810 --> 00:12:32.810
[MUFFLED. INDISTINCT CHATTER]

213
00:12:35.270 --> 00:12:37.110
Okay. you're next. Sit tight.

214
00:12:38.780 --> 00:12:40.440
[BOOMING IN DISTANCE]

215
00:12:41.240 --> 00:12:42.860
Clear that bed!

216
00:12:43.240 --> 00:12:45.570
[ALARM BLARING]
- [CHATTER CONTINUING]

217
00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:51.790
UNA: She didn't make it.

218
00:12:54.420 --> 00:12:55.790
What about the girl?

219
00:12:58.300 --> 00:13:00.340
You're bleeding.
- I'll be fine.

220
00:13:01.920 --> 00:13:03.930
Thank you. I... I locked up. I just... I...

221
00:13:03.930 --> 00:13:07.050
Forget that. I told the Captain. If you're right. they need you.

222
00:13:07.050 --> 00:13:08.310
Get to the bridge.

223
00:13:13.310 --> 00:13:15.190
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

224
00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:17.900
Pike to Main Cargo Bay. Warp is down. Hemmer.

225
00:13:17.900 --> 00:13:20.360
Securing the processor 1ˢᵗ. Captain. It's not safe under fire.

226
00:13:20.360 --> 00:13:21.990
PIKE: <i>Do it. but get us warp. fast.</i>

227
00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:24.490
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

228
00:13:25.820 --> 00:13:27.990
Shields at 60%.
- Anything?

229
00:13:27.990 --> 00:13:29.710
ZUNIGA: Switching comm control to tactical.

230
00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:31.870
Still no response to hails.

231
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:35.330
How fast can you push impulse?

232
00:13:35.330 --> 00:13:36.670
The starboard nacelle is half-damaged.

233
00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:38.210
I can get us about half speed.

234
00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:39.630
Initiate pattern Echo Zeta.

235
00:13:39.630 --> 00:13:42.210
That's an offensive pattern. Captain. Order a retreat.

236
00:13:42.220 --> 00:13:43.680
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

237
00:13:43.680 --> 00:13:45.080
You have to get shields up and go.

238
00:13:45.080 --> 00:13:46.700
Lieutenant. I understand how this might...

239
00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:48.130
You can't fight them.

240
00:13:48.130 --> 00:13:50.050
Confirmed sightings are rare. and they have never ventured...

241
00:13:50.050 --> 00:13:51.600
into Federation...
- It's the Gorn.

242
00:13:57.520 --> 00:13:58.650
It's the Gorn. sir.

243
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:00.860
It's them. This was a trap.

244
00:14:00.860 --> 00:14:02.370
The hologram. the colonists as bait.

245
00:14:02.380 --> 00:14:04.000
They waited for us to be vulnerable.

246
00:14:08.210 --> 00:14:10.460
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

247
00:14:11.240 --> 00:14:13.200
We're too damaged to stand and fight.

248
00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:17.790
It's what they do 1ˢᵗ...

249
00:14:17.790 --> 00:14:19.840
run you down. use up your resources.

250
00:14:19.840 --> 00:14:22.300
Tire us out. Smart tactic.

251
00:14:22.300 --> 00:14:23.420
And deadly.

252
00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:28.720
We have to find cover. regroup. level the playing field.

253
00:14:29.560 --> 00:14:31.470
You have to trust me. Captain.

254
00:14:32.640 --> 00:14:33.730
Please.

255
00:14:37.690 --> 00:14:39.900
That brown dwarf that you mentioned before...

256
00:14:39.900 --> 00:14:41.520
it's. uh. pretty much a gas giant. right?

257
00:14:41.530 --> 00:14:42.610
Where exactly is it?

258
00:14:44.150 --> 00:14:45.740
200 million kilometers away.

259
00:14:45.740 --> 00:14:48.280
But Captain. it is tethered in orbit around a black hole.

260
00:14:48.280 --> 00:14:50.740
Like. how big of a black hole?

261
00:14:51.490 --> 00:14:53.080
1 problem at a time.

262
00:14:54.370 --> 00:14:56.330
Can we maneuver inside the brown dwarf?

263
00:14:56.330 --> 00:14:59.420
While technically possible. there are a number of dangers involved.

264
00:14:59.420 --> 00:15:00.750
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

265
00:15:01.460 --> 00:15:02.550
[ALARM BEEPING]

266
00:15:02.550 --> 00:15:04.130
Shields at 40%.

267
00:15:04.130 --> 00:15:05.300
Bottom-line it for me.

268
00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:06.800
The central mass of the brown dwarf...

269
00:15:06.800 --> 00:15:08.680
has a density that will crush the entire ship.

270
00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:10.300
Surrounding that is a volatile gas cloud.

271
00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:11.470
How volatile?

272
00:15:11.470 --> 00:15:13.430
<i>Enterprise</i> will need to lower its electrical output.

273
00:15:13.430 --> 00:15:15.810
Primary and auxiliary systems need to go offline.

274
00:15:15.810 --> 00:15:18.600
We will lose sensors. optics. long-range communications...

275
00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:19.940
and. most importantly. the shields.

276
00:15:19.940 --> 00:15:21.320
We'll be running dark.

277
00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:23.730
That sounds...
- Perfect.

278
00:15:23.740 --> 00:15:25.900
Anything following us will have to do the same.

279
00:15:25.900 --> 00:15:27.780
If you're right. it's our best shot.

280
00:15:27.780 --> 00:15:29.990
You're the acting Number One again. Do you concur?

281
00:15:29.990 --> 00:15:31.450
Yes. sir.

282
00:15:31.450 --> 00:15:33.660
Helm. full impulse to Spock's mark.

283
00:15:33.660 --> 00:15:35.540
Aye. aye. Full impulse.

284
00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:38.330
Into a giant gas cloud of death.

285
00:15:38.790 --> 00:15:39.790
Why not?

286
00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:42.460
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

287
00:15:58.480 --> 00:16:01.070
Captain. Sickbay and their cargo stores just took direct fire.

288
00:16:04.360 --> 00:16:05.990
As did the main cargo bay.

289
00:16:06.650 --> 00:16:08.660
[ALARMS BLARING]

290
00:16:23.920 --> 00:16:26.220
Lieutenant Hemmer? Lieutenant Hemmer?

291
00:16:26.800 --> 00:16:28.130
[HEMMER GROANS]

292
00:16:29.680 --> 00:16:31.390
Please get this off me.

293
00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:34.390
[GROANING. GRUNTING]

294
00:16:36.310 --> 00:16:37.980
[GRUNTING]

295
00:16:43.400 --> 00:16:44.400
[GROANS]

296
00:16:47.110 --> 00:16:48.280
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

297
00:16:48.860 --> 00:16:50.950
Oh. It's broken.

298
00:16:50.950 --> 00:16:52.530
Well. let's get you to Sickbay.

299
00:16:57.620 --> 00:16:59.630
The door is blocked. isn't it?
- Yep.

300
00:17:01.170 --> 00:17:03.670
[MACHINE WHIRRS DOWN]
- [NEW ALARMS BLARING]

301
00:17:07.880 --> 00:17:09.300
How long before it blows?

302
00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:11.010
<i>I have time to stabilize the unit.</i>

303
00:17:11.680 --> 00:17:13.010
An explosion of that magnitude...

304
00:17:13.010 --> 00:17:16.310
<i>Would consume the</i> Enterprise <i>in an atomic blast. Yes.</i>

305
00:17:16.310 --> 00:17:19.350
Transporters are offline. We'll send in a team to dig you out.

306
00:17:19.350 --> 00:17:21.400
<i>Either way. I'll be here repairing.</i>

307
00:17:21.400 --> 00:17:22.610
<i>Hemmer out.</i>

308
00:17:23.110 --> 00:17:24.730
Is it just me or is it hot in here?

309
00:17:25.230 --> 00:17:28.610
The ionic gas surrounding the ship is overwhelming climate controls.

310
00:17:28.610 --> 00:17:31.280
Many systems are down.
<i>- Including Sickbay.</i>

311
00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:33.160
<i>Everything is offline.</i>

312
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:34.790
<i>We're stabilizing patients...</i>

313
00:17:34.790 --> 00:17:38.370
<i>but without medical systems. no one is getting better.</i>

314
00:17:38.370 --> 00:17:39.540
<i>It's triage.</i>

315
00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:41.250
Casualties?

316
00:17:41.250 --> 00:17:43.630
<i>Yes. Captain. 9 confirmed.</i>

317
00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:47.760
<i>The hit we took decimated our stock of treatment supplies.</i>

318
00:17:47.760 --> 00:17:50.380
<i>And with the matter synthesizers also offline...</i>

319
00:17:50.390 --> 00:17:52.600
<i>we can't make more when we run out.</i>

320
00:17:53.010 --> 00:17:55.390
How's Una?
<i>- She reports that she's fine.</i>

321
00:17:55.390 --> 00:17:56.810
<i>She's on her way in.</i>

322
00:17:56.810 --> 00:17:58.480
<i>I haven't had time to check her yet.</i>

323
00:17:58.480 --> 00:18:00.270
<i>We're still playing catch-up.</i>

324
00:18:00.270 --> 00:18:02.690
<i>I've activated all backup medical personnel...</i>

325
00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:05.650
<i>but what I really need down here are supplies.</i>

326
00:18:05.650 --> 00:18:08.190
CHAPEL: <i>Doctor. I could really use some help over here.</i>

327
00:18:08.200 --> 00:18:09.780
<i>M'Benga out.</i>

328
00:18:15.950 --> 00:18:17.960
[ALARM BLARING]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

329
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:25.380
Doctor!

330
00:18:30.430 --> 00:18:32.800
You said you were fine.
- I was mistaken.

331
00:18:32.800 --> 00:18:33.850
These are deep.

332
00:18:35.310 --> 00:18:37.100
We can't power up the surgery bays.

333
00:18:41.020 --> 00:18:44.110
If I recall. you have an interest in archeological medicine.

334
00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:48.150
How good are you at sewing?

335
00:18:49.200 --> 00:18:50.410
Aces.

336
00:18:53.410 --> 00:18:55.580
[BREATHING SHALLOWLY]

337
00:18:55.580 --> 00:18:57.700
No weapons systems. no phasers.

338
00:18:58.330 --> 00:19:00.540
What about photon torpedoes? Those can be self-guided.

339
00:19:00.540 --> 00:19:03.710
The torpedo bay was hit in the attack. We lost all but 1.

340
00:19:04.460 --> 00:19:06.710
We only have 1 photon torpedo?

341
00:19:07.340 --> 00:19:09.130
SPOCK: The amount is inconsequential.

342
00:19:09.130 --> 00:19:11.340
If we fire a torpedo inside the brown dwarf...

343
00:19:11.340 --> 00:19:14.510
the atmospheric composition will cause a failure in the internal systems.

344
00:19:14.510 --> 00:19:17.720
It would propel in a random direction. likely missing its intended target.

345
00:19:17.730 --> 00:19:20.770
So. no shields and no weapons.

346
00:19:21.650 --> 00:19:23.350
What do we do?

347
00:19:23.360 --> 00:19:25.360
Throw luggage at them?

348
00:19:26.030 --> 00:19:28.780
And the Gorn. really? We're out here fighting...

349
00:19:28.780 --> 00:19:30.900
the boogeyman? No one has even seen one.

350
00:19:30.910 --> 00:19:33.110
So how are we supposed to take them on?

351
00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:34.370
I've seen them.

352
00:19:36.950 --> 00:19:38.620
They aren't supernatural.

353
00:19:39.330 --> 00:19:41.580
But they are monsters.

354
00:19:43.790 --> 00:19:45.290
The Federation teaches that...

355
00:19:45.290 --> 00:19:47.880
if we can find a way to empathize with an enemy...

356
00:19:47.880 --> 00:19:49.720
then they can one day become our friends.

357
00:19:50.380 --> 00:19:51.630
They're wrong.

358
00:19:52.220 --> 00:19:55.050
Some things in this universe are just plain evil.

359
00:19:55.640 --> 00:19:59.390
Have you ever seen eyes that are both dead and hungry at the same time?

360
00:19:59.390 --> 00:20:02.390
To them. humans are just walking feed bags...

361
00:20:02.400 --> 00:20:05.400
of flesh and bone and jelly.

362
00:20:06.150 --> 00:20:08.440
The Gorn trigger a primitive. ancient. terror...

363
00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:10.150
in warm-blooded species.

364
00:20:10.150 --> 00:20:12.360
We are prey.

365
00:20:13.240 --> 00:20:15.410
And when they hunt. they're unrelenting.

366
00:20:15.950 --> 00:20:19.080
The truth is. plenty of people have seen the Gorn.

367
00:20:20.370 --> 00:20:22.460
They just don't live long enough to talk about it.

368
00:20:27.880 --> 00:20:29.090
All right.

369
00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:32.800
Be vigilant.

370
00:20:33.260 --> 00:20:34.590
Get creative.

371
00:20:35.470 --> 00:20:37.100
You're the best of Starfleet.

372
00:20:37.100 --> 00:20:38.770
We survive this by working together.

373
00:20:44.980 --> 00:20:46.230
[DOOR WHOOSHES OPEN]

374
00:20:46.230 --> 00:20:47.860
A moment. Lieutenant.

375
00:20:48.780 --> 00:20:49.940
[DOOR WHOOSHES CLOSED]

376
00:20:52.150 --> 00:20:53.490
How you holding up?

377
00:20:54.950 --> 00:20:56.950
The enemy doesn't care about my feelings. Captain...

378
00:20:56.950 --> 00:20:58.620
so I don't waste my time having any.

379
00:20:59.700 --> 00:21:03.290
Well. that may be true. but it's not looking that way to the crew.

380
00:21:03.880 --> 00:21:05.290
With all due respect...

381
00:21:05.290 --> 00:21:07.130
you know me well enough to know that I don't care...

382
00:21:07.130 --> 00:21:08.460
what the crew thinks.

383
00:21:08.460 --> 00:21:10.710
I've always been blunt. That's just who I am.

384
00:21:10.720 --> 00:21:13.300
Direct. looking at outcomes. not emotion.

385
00:21:13.300 --> 00:21:14.430
Exactly.

386
00:21:14.430 --> 00:21:17.310
But right now. your job isn't just about orders. it's about hope.

387
00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:21.140
Belief can be the difference between victory and defeat.

388
00:21:22.230 --> 00:21:24.940
Get a crew to believe in miracles. they might just give you one.

389
00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:27.820
I will make that adjustment.

390
00:21:28.530 --> 00:21:30.150
But I will not lie to them.

391
00:21:32.150 --> 00:21:34.280
The best miracles are born from truth.

392
00:21:35.780 --> 00:21:37.030
Understood. Captain.

393
00:21:37.950 --> 00:21:39.950
Now. there's not much on the official record.

394
00:21:41.460 --> 00:21:43.330
Is there anything else you can remember...

395
00:21:43.710 --> 00:21:45.000
from your time with the Gorn...

396
00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:46.170
anything that might help?

397
00:21:49.460 --> 00:21:52.050
The memories of what happened are. um...

398
00:21:52.670 --> 00:21:54.720
trauma-inhibited. It's all...

399
00:21:55.140 --> 00:21:58.050
It's... It's all fragments.

400
00:21:58.060 --> 00:21:59.640
Bits and pieces.

401
00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:03.350
Well. if anything comes to mind.

402
00:22:09.230 --> 00:22:10.570
[ALARMS BLARING]

403
00:22:12.150 --> 00:22:13.320
[GROANS SOFTLY]

404
00:22:14.950 --> 00:22:18.740
An engineer's most important tools are his mind and his hands.

405
00:22:19.410 --> 00:22:21.370
And I can't move my fingers.

406
00:22:21.370 --> 00:22:24.210
[GROANS]
- Oh... Okay.

407
00:22:24.210 --> 00:22:26.040
Let's just...

408
00:22:27.210 --> 00:22:29.550
work on relaxing.

409
00:22:31.130 --> 00:22:32.590
[NEW ALARM BEEPING]

410
00:22:34.880 --> 00:22:36.140
Here's what's gonna happen.

411
00:22:36.680 --> 00:22:38.390
You're gonna talk me through what to do.

412
00:22:38.930 --> 00:22:40.010
We're gonna be a team.

413
00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:41.560
It's not that simple.

414
00:22:41.560 --> 00:22:43.890
There's a variety of data that only I can assess.

415
00:22:43.890 --> 00:22:46.400
And I'm the only one here with a working set of fingers.

416
00:22:47.310 --> 00:22:48.900
I am not fond of teams.

417
00:22:50.070 --> 00:22:51.240
Get fond.

418
00:22:51.900 --> 00:22:53.150
It would seem I have to.

419
00:22:55.240 --> 00:22:59.780
Start by using the control panel to shut down the safety override.

420
00:22:59.790 --> 00:23:02.540
You'll have to adjust the cooling system.

421
00:23:02.540 --> 00:23:03.870
[BEEPING]

422
00:23:07.170 --> 00:23:08.500
What did I do?

423
00:23:08.500 --> 00:23:11.460
Your other hand operates the cooling system as you work.

424
00:23:11.460 --> 00:23:13.670
Take the time to get focused.

425
00:23:13.670 --> 00:23:16.720
Don't let the core get above 110°.

426
00:23:20.890 --> 00:23:21.970
[BOATSWAIN'S WHISTLE BLOWS]

427
00:23:21.970 --> 00:23:24.060
Captain. a moment please?

428
00:23:24.060 --> 00:23:25.440
You have something. Spock?

429
00:23:25.440 --> 00:23:26.980
You challenged us to get creative.

430
00:23:27.810 --> 00:23:30.070
Computer. run program Vinci 7.

431
00:23:30.070 --> 00:23:31.440
[SYSTEM BEEPING]

432
00:23:33.990 --> 00:23:35.990
Primary sensors aren't available.

433
00:23:35.990 --> 00:23:38.700
But navigation systems constantly take in atmospheric data...

434
00:23:38.700 --> 00:23:40.120
to maintain stability.

435
00:23:40.120 --> 00:23:42.120
Hey. I still do most of the work.

436
00:23:42.870 --> 00:23:45.210
A ship traveling through the gas cloud creates...

437
00:23:45.210 --> 00:23:46.960
oscillation in the atmosphere.

438
00:23:46.960 --> 00:23:49.170
These are converted into rotational motions by...

439
00:23:49.170 --> 00:23:50.710
Coriolis forces.

440
00:23:50.710 --> 00:23:53.130
Which the nav-comm detects automatically.

441
00:23:53.130 --> 00:23:56.010
Marking Coriolis force readings would allow us to triangulate...

442
00:23:56.010 --> 00:23:59.300
movement inside the gas giant. We can track the Gorn.

443
00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:03.270
You just turned a compass into a radar.

444
00:24:04.310 --> 00:24:05.520
Do it.

445
00:24:11.360 --> 00:24:12.690
[BEEPING]

446
00:24:13.110 --> 00:24:14.740
It's working. We've got a signal.

447
00:24:14.740 --> 00:24:15.950
Analysis?

448
00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:19.660
The size and speed indicate it is the ship that attacked us.

449
00:24:22.790 --> 00:24:24.540
They're coming right at us.

450
00:24:26.500 --> 00:24:28.210
ETA is 1 minute.

451
00:24:28.210 --> 00:24:29.340
Can they see us?

452
00:24:30.040 --> 00:24:31.540
It is impossible to tell. Captain.

453
00:24:31.550 --> 00:24:33.550
Captain. evasive maneuvers?

454
00:24:34.300 --> 00:24:35.800
Negative. Keep her steady.

455
00:24:43.270 --> 00:24:44.310
Captain.

456
00:24:46.270 --> 00:24:48.520
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

457
00:24:57.860 --> 00:24:59.740
Preparing to engage the enemy.

458
00:25:01.120 --> 00:25:02.700
Keep her steady. Helm.

459
00:25:04.370 --> 00:25:05.710
Aye.

460
00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:12.500
The enemy has altered its course.

461
00:25:13.880 --> 00:25:15.300
They can't see us.

462
00:25:15.300 --> 00:25:17.180
But they won't stop looking.

463
00:25:20.140 --> 00:25:22.050
Zuniga. arm the last torpedo.

464
00:25:22.060 --> 00:25:23.560
Arming torpedo.

465
00:25:24.980 --> 00:25:26.850
Captain. I must remind you...

466
00:25:26.850 --> 00:25:29.560
that if you fire a photon torpedo inside a brown dwarf...

467
00:25:29.560 --> 00:25:31.110
the guidance systems will not work.

468
00:25:31.820 --> 00:25:33.570
I don't plan on firing it.

469
00:25:33.570 --> 00:25:35.530
We're gonna drop it on them manually.

470
00:25:36.900 --> 00:25:38.410
Now we're talking.

471
00:25:38.910 --> 00:25:40.530
PIKE: Set a course to pursue the enemy vessel.

472
00:25:40.530 --> 00:25:41.870
Quick but quiet. Erica.

473
00:25:41.870 --> 00:25:43.620
That is my specialty.

474
00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:51.920
PIKE: Put us right over her...

475
00:25:51.920 --> 00:25:53.710
then tilt axis 90°.

476
00:25:54.960 --> 00:25:56.090
Once the hatch opens...

477
00:25:56.090 --> 00:25:58.340
the higher mass below should pull the torpedo straight down.

478
00:25:58.340 --> 00:25:59.470
On my mark.

479
00:26:18.780 --> 00:26:19.990
Deploy torpedo.

480
00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:22.780
Bombs away.

481
00:26:30.750 --> 00:26:31.920
[RUMBLES]

482
00:26:37.550 --> 00:26:38.880
The signal is gone.

483
00:26:38.880 --> 00:26:40.680
The enemy ship has been destroyed.

484
00:26:47.480 --> 00:26:48.810
[BEEPING]

485
00:26:52.110 --> 00:26:53.560
Captain. we have incoming.

486
00:26:53.570 --> 00:26:54.980
Multiple incoming.

487
00:26:59.360 --> 00:27:00.820
They wanted us to fire.

488
00:27:02.490 --> 00:27:05.450
They sacrificed an entire ship just to get our location.

489
00:27:05.450 --> 00:27:07.960
ORTEGAS: Why is that blip so much bigger?

490
00:27:21.640 --> 00:27:24.050
[ALARM BLARING]

491
00:27:24.060 --> 00:27:26.060
3 on 1. Not good.

492
00:27:26.060 --> 00:27:28.060
We're outgunned. Time to run. sir.

493
00:27:28.060 --> 00:27:30.940
I concur. But if we leave the brown dwarf they will see us.

494
00:27:30.940 --> 00:27:32.980
If we go deeper. it could destroy the ship.

495
00:27:32.980 --> 00:27:34.400
Good thinking. Mr. Spock.

496
00:27:34.730 --> 00:27:36.780
We need to go deeper into the brown dwarf.

497
00:27:37.360 --> 00:27:38.740
That is not what I suggested.

498
00:27:38.740 --> 00:27:40.400
Ortegas. plot a course.

499
00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:42.200
As close as you can get us to center mass.

500
00:27:42.200 --> 00:27:43.320
Sure.

501
00:27:43.330 --> 00:27:46.040
Didn't our science expert just say that would crush the ship?

502
00:27:46.500 --> 00:27:48.710
Just asking. sir.
- SPOCK: I did.

503
00:27:48.710 --> 00:27:51.580
The pressure against the hull will increase the deeper we go.

504
00:27:51.580 --> 00:27:54.380
If we venture too close. the density field will obliterate us.

505
00:27:54.380 --> 00:27:56.760
Whatever happens to us will also happen to the Gorn.

506
00:27:57.130 --> 00:27:58.550
I believe in <i>Enterprise.</i>

507
00:27:59.630 --> 00:28:01.260
We can outlast them.

508
00:28:01.260 --> 00:28:04.260
Captain. the lower decks will be 1ˢᵗ to take structural damage.

509
00:28:04.260 --> 00:28:06.220
Immediate evacuation of all decks below 20.

510
00:28:07.060 --> 00:28:09.680
I don't like it either. but <i>Enterprise</i> has to dive.

511
00:28:09.690 --> 00:28:11.060
Helm. take us down.

512
00:28:11.060 --> 00:28:13.690
Aye. aye. Skipper. Dive. dive. dive.

513
00:28:15.900 --> 00:28:17.570
[ALARM CONTINUES BLARING]

514
00:28:17.940 --> 00:28:19.110
[UNA WINCES]

515
00:28:22.570 --> 00:28:24.580
[METAL GROANING]

516
00:28:31.750 --> 00:28:32.750
[UNA GROANS SOFTLY]

517
00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:40.340
[UNA GROANS]

518
00:28:40.340 --> 00:28:41.930
[WALLS RATTLING]

519
00:28:44.930 --> 00:28:47.270
[SHIP GROANS]

520
00:28:48.140 --> 00:28:50.730
I've never heard a ship make a sound like that before.

521
00:28:50.730 --> 00:28:51.770
No.

522
00:28:52.350 --> 00:28:55.060
Keep your focus. And maybe pick up the pace.

523
00:28:55.070 --> 00:28:57.070
[BEEPING]

524
00:28:57.070 --> 00:28:58.230
[ALARM BEEPS]

525
00:28:58.230 --> 00:28:59.990
[EXCLAIMS] This isn't easy. And I...

526
00:28:59.990 --> 00:29:01.990
And. of course. diagnostics are offline.

527
00:29:01.990 --> 00:29:03.660
I can't tell which ones are broken.

528
00:29:03.660 --> 00:29:06.160
Hold your hand out to each. Tell me what you feel.

529
00:29:11.290 --> 00:29:13.670
[SIZZLES]
- Aah! Hot!

530
00:29:13.670 --> 00:29:15.170
I did not say touch them.

531
00:29:15.170 --> 00:29:17.340
The malfunctioning rods should be cool.

532
00:29:17.800 --> 00:29:19.630
Be sure before you remove them.

533
00:29:24.390 --> 00:29:25.800
All right. I think I've got a cold one.

534
00:29:25.810 --> 00:29:29.060
Perfect. Now lift it out gently.

535
00:29:32.940 --> 00:29:35.310
[LAUGHS] Look at us! Come on!

536
00:29:35.310 --> 00:29:36.690
And the crowd goes wild.

537
00:29:37.610 --> 00:29:38.900
Before replacing it...

538
00:29:38.900 --> 00:29:41.900
we have to reconfigure the host platform.

539
00:29:45.620 --> 00:29:48.370
Reconfigure the...

540
00:29:50.080 --> 00:29:51.160
Done.

541
00:29:51.160 --> 00:29:52.830
Now we can get started.

542
00:29:56.000 --> 00:29:57.340
Get started?

543
00:29:58.170 --> 00:30:00.170
[SHIP GROANING]

544
00:30:14.400 --> 00:30:15.900
[ALARM BUZZING]

545
00:30:16.690 --> 00:30:18.520
The lower decks are beginning to buckle.

546
00:30:18.530 --> 00:30:21.240
The evacuation isn't complete. There's still crew down there.

547
00:30:21.240 --> 00:30:22.490
Get them out.

548
00:30:22.490 --> 00:30:23.950
Decks are collapsing.

549
00:30:23.950 --> 00:30:25.320
If we do not seal them off now...

550
00:30:25.320 --> 00:30:27.700
loss of pressure could spread to the entire ship.

551
00:30:31.120 --> 00:30:32.420
Seal the bulkheads.

552
00:30:33.210 --> 00:30:34.420
Sir.

553
00:30:43.470 --> 00:30:44.890
Uh. hey. hey!

554
00:30:45.390 --> 00:30:47.050
Hey.
- [GROANS]

555
00:30:47.050 --> 00:30:48.640
I got you. I got you.

556
00:30:54.310 --> 00:30:57.320
[GRUNTS] Go!
- No. no. no. no! Hey!

557
00:31:03.740 --> 00:31:07.070
Structural collapse on Deck 22. We've lost 1 crew person.

558
00:31:09.790 --> 00:31:11.250
You made the logical choice.

559
00:31:12.330 --> 00:31:13.790
Why doesn't it feel like that?

560
00:31:14.880 --> 00:31:17.880
For the same reason you made it. Because you value life.

561
00:31:17.880 --> 00:31:20.420
Captain. we're approaching critical hull failure.

562
00:31:20.420 --> 00:31:22.300
If antimatter chambers become compromised...

563
00:31:22.300 --> 00:31:23.630
there will be no ship left to save.

564
00:31:23.630 --> 00:31:25.050
LA'AN: <i>Enterprise</i> can't take much more of this.

565
00:31:25.050 --> 00:31:26.260
We're overextended.

566
00:31:29.180 --> 00:31:31.390
You said they wanted to take us prisoner. Number One?

567
00:31:32.850 --> 00:31:34.850
Well. if they think they're gonna board the <i>Enterprise</i>...

568
00:31:34.850 --> 00:31:37.400
they're gonna find one hell of a fight. Battle stations.

569
00:31:37.400 --> 00:31:38.860
Make ready for close quarters.

570
00:31:42.650 --> 00:31:45.110
Ortegas. full stop.

571
00:31:45.110 --> 00:31:46.620
Aye. sir. Full stop.

572
00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:48.830
[ENGINES POWER DOWN]

573
00:31:55.210 --> 00:31:57.130
Captain. The enemy ship.

574
00:32:01.880 --> 00:32:03.880
[METAL GROANING]

575
00:32:12.180 --> 00:32:14.140
It appears the Gorn vessel could not withstand...

576
00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:16.310
the atmospheric pressure. It has imploded.

577
00:32:22.070 --> 00:32:25.200
You said when the Gorn hunt they are relentless.

578
00:32:25.200 --> 00:32:26.360
They don't stop.

579
00:32:26.780 --> 00:32:29.080
You exploited that as a weakness.

580
00:32:29.580 --> 00:32:30.990
Get me a damage report.

581
00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:32.910
Mr. Spock. keep scanning for the other 2 ships.

582
00:32:43.170 --> 00:32:46.090
2 down. 2 to go. Doing good.

583
00:32:51.680 --> 00:32:52.980
How's it going?

584
00:32:53.810 --> 00:32:55.890
Feel a little like Frankenstein's monster...

585
00:32:55.890 --> 00:32:57.350
but I'll be all right.

586
00:32:58.110 --> 00:32:59.690
There's 1 fragment left.

587
00:33:00.690 --> 00:33:02.860
The intrusion on her abdominal aorta.

588
00:33:06.950 --> 00:33:08.450
Okay. what are you not telling me?

589
00:33:08.450 --> 00:33:09.820
We need to sedate you.

590
00:33:09.830 --> 00:33:11.120
The location of the fragment...

591
00:33:11.120 --> 00:33:12.700
You're gonna bleed. A lot.

592
00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:17.960
We have just enough plasma...

593
00:33:19.040 --> 00:33:21.130
but we're gonna have to give it to you via IV.

594
00:33:21.130 --> 00:33:22.460
Do I have a choice?

595
00:33:23.630 --> 00:33:24.840
M'BENGA: You can decline.

596
00:33:25.220 --> 00:33:26.760
Wait for the systems to be online.

597
00:33:26.760 --> 00:33:29.300
CHAPEL: We can take bets on when septic shock will begin.

598
00:33:29.300 --> 00:33:31.310
I hear it's like giving birth out your mouth.

599
00:33:31.310 --> 00:33:33.220
Who says something like that?

600
00:33:34.810 --> 00:33:35.890
Me.

601
00:33:37.230 --> 00:33:38.610
Give me the gas.

602
00:33:40.230 --> 00:33:41.360
Okay.

603
00:33:41.940 --> 00:33:43.650
[GAS HISSES]

604
00:33:43.650 --> 00:33:45.900
Just breathe. You'll start to feel drowsy.

605
00:33:45.900 --> 00:33:48.200
Nurse. She needs plasma.

606
00:33:48.200 --> 00:33:49.530
There's none left.

607
00:33:53.040 --> 00:33:54.330
Give her mine.

608
00:33:54.330 --> 00:33:55.660
It's the last one.

609
00:33:55.660 --> 00:33:57.960
You're about to lose a massive amount of blood.

610
00:33:58.500 --> 00:33:59.880
That's an order.

611
00:34:10.100 --> 00:34:11.810
PIKE: <i>Captain's Log. supplemental.</i>

612
00:34:11.810 --> 00:34:14.270
Enterprise <i>is currently in the center of a gas giant...</i>

613
00:34:14.270 --> 00:34:16.600
<i>hiding from an enemy we've never faced before.</i>

614
00:34:18.940 --> 00:34:21.440
<i>So far. 3 civilians and 7 of my crew...</i>

615
00:34:21.440 --> 00:34:22.730
<i>have lost their lives.</i>

616
00:34:24.240 --> 00:34:25.740
<i>The battle is far from over.</i>

617
00:34:26.450 --> 00:34:29.240
<i>But I am determined to keep everyone else alive.</i>

618
00:34:31.580 --> 00:34:34.830
<i>My newest obstacle is the presence of a nearby black hole.</i>

619
00:34:35.290 --> 00:34:37.120
Atmospheric density is decreasing.

620
00:34:37.120 --> 00:34:39.120
I believe the singularity is advancing...

621
00:34:39.130 --> 00:34:41.130
its accumulation of substellar material.

622
00:34:42.300 --> 00:34:44.260
Do you ever speak in plain English?

623
00:34:46.300 --> 00:34:49.680
The brown dwarf we're hiding inside is being sucked into a black hole.

624
00:34:49.680 --> 00:34:50.970
We stay. we will go with it.

625
00:34:51.970 --> 00:34:53.060
Precisely.

626
00:34:53.060 --> 00:34:54.430
LA'AN: And we can't pop our heads up...

627
00:34:54.430 --> 00:34:56.730
to see if it's clear to leave. They could see us.

628
00:34:56.730 --> 00:34:59.440
Without long-range communication. we cannot even send a probe.

629
00:35:00.770 --> 00:35:03.650
How much time before we can't escape the black hole's gravity?

630
00:35:03.650 --> 00:35:05.480
1 hour. 32 minutes and 48 seconds.

631
00:35:05.490 --> 00:35:06.650
What about a shuttle?

632
00:35:07.490 --> 00:35:09.660
Small enough to navigate undetected.

633
00:35:09.660 --> 00:35:11.570
Minimize risk to the rest of the crew.

634
00:35:11.580 --> 00:35:13.530
That sounds like a suicide mission.

635
00:35:13.540 --> 00:35:15.910
LA'AN: Captain. a shuttle is our only shot.

636
00:35:15.910 --> 00:35:17.870
You don't have to order anyone to go.

637
00:35:19.330 --> 00:35:20.540
I'll do it.

638
00:35:20.540 --> 00:35:21.710
As will I.

639
00:35:22.460 --> 00:35:24.800
To put it in plain English. you will need backup.

640
00:35:30.180 --> 00:35:31.550
Take the <i>Galileo.</i>

641
00:35:32.010 --> 00:35:33.850
Get back here in 30 minutes. no matter what.

642
00:35:34.970 --> 00:35:36.180
Sir.

643
00:35:49.200 --> 00:35:50.530
[SOFT WHIRRING]

644
00:36:07.170 --> 00:36:08.550
SPOCK: Fascinating.

645
00:36:08.550 --> 00:36:10.090
Why scan each other?

646
00:36:10.720 --> 00:36:12.850
LA'AN: No. It's not a scan. it's...

647
00:36:14.560 --> 00:36:15.810
something else.

648
00:36:16.180 --> 00:36:18.980
You've seen this before. when you were attacked by the Gorn.

649
00:36:18.980 --> 00:36:21.060
The <i>S.S. Puget Sound.</i>

650
00:36:22.020 --> 00:36:23.820
That was the name of our colony ship.

651
00:36:28.650 --> 00:36:30.610
I remember some. A lot of it is just...

652
00:36:31.160 --> 00:36:32.780
flashes in the dark.

653
00:36:32.780 --> 00:36:35.450
But I know I've seen those lights.

654
00:36:35.450 --> 00:36:36.700
The mind is complex.

655
00:36:36.700 --> 00:36:38.410
When faced with intense trauma...

656
00:36:38.410 --> 00:36:40.870
it can manifest intricate defenses to aid survival.

657
00:36:43.540 --> 00:36:45.210
I feel like there's something in there.

658
00:36:46.630 --> 00:36:48.090
Something I should know.

659
00:36:49.220 --> 00:36:51.760
Understandable. given the enemy we are currently facing.

660
00:36:52.550 --> 00:36:53.930
You can help me.

661
00:36:55.930 --> 00:36:57.720
I've heard what Vulcans can do.

662
00:36:57.730 --> 00:37:00.850
The mind meld is not a shortcut for dealing with mental trauma.

663
00:37:01.600 --> 00:37:04.570
Resurfacing hidden memories can be painful...

664
00:37:04.570 --> 00:37:05.900
even dangerous.

665
00:37:05.900 --> 00:37:08.940
If somewhere in my head is the answer to saving the <i>Enterprise</i>...

666
00:37:08.950 --> 00:37:10.450
then that's a risk I have to take.

667
00:37:10.450 --> 00:37:11.950
I can't just keep running.

668
00:37:27.090 --> 00:37:29.720
SPOCK: My mind to your mind.

669
00:37:30.550 --> 00:37:32.800
My thoughts to your thoughts.

670
00:37:33.430 --> 00:37:36.970
<i>My mind to your thoughts. To your...</i>

671
00:37:36.970 --> 00:37:39.350
[VOICE GROWS DISTORTED. DISTANT]

672
00:37:39.350 --> 00:37:40.810
GIRL: <i>Mom?</i>

673
00:37:40.810 --> 00:37:43.270
WOMAN: <i>La'An. be brave.</i>
- MAN: <i>Evacuate the ship!</i>

674
00:37:43.270 --> 00:37:46.020
LA'AN: <i>Not believing you're gonna die is what gets you killed.</i>

675
00:37:46.030 --> 00:37:48.150
SPOCK: Your memories are starting to surface.

676
00:37:52.820 --> 00:37:54.450
This is a Gorn breeding planet.

677
00:37:59.620 --> 00:38:01.870
They brought us here as food for their hatchlings.

678
00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:05.500
Hunted us day and night.

679
00:38:13.760 --> 00:38:16.720
Your mind is resisting. You are...

680
00:38:17.180 --> 00:38:18.220
Scared.

681
00:38:21.020 --> 00:38:22.350
I don't like this place.

682
00:38:24.020 --> 00:38:25.480
Do you want to stop?

683
00:38:28.150 --> 00:38:29.320
No.

684
00:38:30.530 --> 00:38:31.820
I can do this.

685
00:38:33.910 --> 00:38:35.370
I need to know.

686
00:38:44.540 --> 00:38:46.210
[SHUDDERING BREATHS]

687
00:38:47.250 --> 00:38:48.920
[PANTING]

688
00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:51.760
[DISTANT CLICKING]

689
00:38:56.890 --> 00:38:58.890
[GRUNTS]
- [DISTANT SCREECH]

690
00:39:04.770 --> 00:39:07.150
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

691
00:39:07.150 --> 00:39:08.820
I was trying to be quiet.
- It's okay.

692
00:39:08.820 --> 00:39:10.240
[GROWLING. CLUCKING]
- I was trying to be quiet.

693
00:39:10.240 --> 00:39:11.320
It's okay. it's okay.

694
00:39:11.320 --> 00:39:13.740
It's okay. Look at me. La'An. it's okay.

695
00:39:13.740 --> 00:39:16.030
Right here. Right here. right here. right here.

696
00:39:16.030 --> 00:39:17.950
Keep looking at me.
- They're coming.

697
00:39:18.580 --> 00:39:20.080
Take this.

698
00:39:20.080 --> 00:39:21.750
It'll help you hide.

699
00:39:21.750 --> 00:39:23.920
The lights. I watched them.

700
00:39:23.920 --> 00:39:26.000
It's how they talk to each other.

701
00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:27.420
It's all in there.

702
00:39:27.420 --> 00:39:29.000
What are you doing?

703
00:39:29.010 --> 00:39:30.090
You need to run.

704
00:39:30.090 --> 00:39:31.920
Don't be afraid. Don't look back.

705
00:39:32.630 --> 00:39:35.550
Just run. Keep moving. no matter what.

706
00:39:35.550 --> 00:39:36.720
Okay?

707
00:39:39.470 --> 00:39:41.440
Come with me.
- I can't.

708
00:40:07.920 --> 00:40:09.130
Run. La'An.

709
00:40:09.130 --> 00:40:10.510
Run!

710
00:40:12.970 --> 00:40:14.630
[THUNDER CRASHING]

711
00:40:16.890 --> 00:40:17.970
What happened?

712
00:40:20.220 --> 00:40:23.940
Your subconscious is setting a boundary.

713
00:40:26.610 --> 00:40:28.480
The lights. they're a code.

714
00:40:28.480 --> 00:40:30.570
My brother showed me how to read it.

715
00:40:32.530 --> 00:40:34.360
[SPOCK SPEAKING VULCAN]

716
00:40:37.990 --> 00:40:40.240
BURNHAM: <i>I love you too. brother.</i>

717
00:40:49.050 --> 00:40:51.010
You lost someone too. didn't you?

718
00:40:53.510 --> 00:40:54.590
You had...

719
00:40:55.340 --> 00:40:56.680
a sister.

720
00:40:58.350 --> 00:41:00.470
But Starfleet records don't show any...

721
00:41:00.470 --> 00:41:01.640
They do not.

722
00:41:06.440 --> 00:41:09.020
She sacrificed herself for you. too. didn't she?

723
00:41:11.690 --> 00:41:13.820
I think we should end this mind meld now.

724
00:41:20.200 --> 00:41:21.870
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

725
00:41:25.960 --> 00:41:27.460
Spock. I have an idea.

726
00:41:36.140 --> 00:41:38.550
I've modulated the shuttle's phasers per your instruction.

727
00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:41.310
Surprised you agreed to this.

728
00:41:41.310 --> 00:41:43.060
I believe it is a good plan.

729
00:41:44.060 --> 00:41:46.100
And our mind meld reminded me of risks taken...

730
00:41:46.100 --> 00:41:47.940
and their value to those that survive.

731
00:41:50.780 --> 00:41:52.110
[SOFT BEEPING]

732
00:41:55.530 --> 00:41:58.570
LA'AN: I just told them humans boarded and took over the vessel.

733
00:41:58.580 --> 00:42:00.280
At least I hope I did.

734
00:42:00.290 --> 00:42:02.410
Culling the weak makes them stronger.

735
00:42:03.250 --> 00:42:04.580
Survival of the fittest.

736
00:42:25.690 --> 00:42:28.480
[BEEPING]
- [ALARMS BLARING]

737
00:42:32.190 --> 00:42:35.450
[SIGHS] And Uhura for the win.

738
00:42:36.320 --> 00:42:39.120
[GROANING SOFTLY]
- Oh. stay awake.

739
00:42:39.120 --> 00:42:41.410
Okay? Let's get you talking.

740
00:42:42.040 --> 00:42:43.200
Uh...

741
00:42:43.200 --> 00:42:47.460
So. an Aenar in Starfleet. how's that even work?

742
00:42:48.080 --> 00:42:49.710
Thought you guys were all pacifists.

743
00:42:51.000 --> 00:42:52.960
I actually wanted to be a botanist.

744
00:42:54.380 --> 00:42:55.470
I love flora.

745
00:42:57.300 --> 00:42:59.800
I will not fight for Starfleet.

746
00:43:00.800 --> 00:43:02.470
But I will defend its ideals.

747
00:43:03.020 --> 00:43:05.060
Pacifism is not passivity.

748
00:43:05.060 --> 00:43:06.980
It is the active protection...

749
00:43:06.980 --> 00:43:09.150
of all living things in the natural universe.

750
00:43:11.400 --> 00:43:12.860
A matter of perspective.

751
00:43:13.990 --> 00:43:15.950
Like using touch instead of sight.

752
00:43:18.410 --> 00:43:19.660
I wouldn't know.

753
00:43:19.660 --> 00:43:22.490
[NEW ALARM BLARING]
- [SIZZLING]

754
00:43:22.490 --> 00:43:26.210
The matrix exceeded critical limits before we completed repairs.

755
00:43:26.210 --> 00:43:27.870
Our only option now is to vent...

756
00:43:27.870 --> 00:43:30.250
this bay and everything in it into space.

757
00:43:30.250 --> 00:43:31.420
But...

758
00:43:32.670 --> 00:43:34.050
we're in here. too.

759
00:43:35.010 --> 00:43:38.260
Unfortunately. that is also true.

760
00:43:42.970 --> 00:43:46.350
<i>We have 20 minutes until the unit explodes. Maybe less.</i>

761
00:43:46.350 --> 00:43:47.850
PIKE: Acknowledged. Stand by.

762
00:43:49.150 --> 00:43:50.860
Welcome back. Lieutenants. Good job.

763
00:43:50.860 --> 00:43:52.320
Though we're not out of the woods yet.

764
00:43:52.320 --> 00:43:54.240
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

765
00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:56.780
Report.

766
00:43:56.780 --> 00:43:58.990
It's not the Gorn. It's this guy.

767
00:44:00.950 --> 00:44:02.870
The brown dwarf is dissolving too fast.

768
00:44:02.870 --> 00:44:04.120
We are losing our cover.

769
00:44:04.120 --> 00:44:06.800
We don't get out of here pretty fast. we're gonna be sitting ducks.

770
00:44:07.040 --> 00:44:09.000
Except that last Gorn ship will be on top of us...

771
00:44:09.000 --> 00:44:10.330
the instant we leave.

772
00:44:10.330 --> 00:44:12.800
[SIGHS] Space really wants us dead.

773
00:44:13.750 --> 00:44:15.210
Then why don't we let space win?

774
00:44:16.090 --> 00:44:18.680
Spock. could we use the black hole's gravity...

775
00:44:18.680 --> 00:44:20.140
to slingshot us to safety?

776
00:44:20.140 --> 00:44:21.720
Mathematically. that is possible.

777
00:44:21.720 --> 00:44:24.850
But the Gorn will see us and have the opportunity to pursue us.

778
00:44:24.850 --> 00:44:26.640
Maybe.
- Maybe?

779
00:44:27.270 --> 00:44:29.060
Explain gravitational redshift.

780
00:44:29.060 --> 00:44:31.360
Gravitational redshift is an optical illusion...

781
00:44:31.360 --> 00:44:33.690
that occurs as an object falls into a black hole.

782
00:44:33.690 --> 00:44:36.030
The object falls faster than the frequency of light it emits.

783
00:44:36.030 --> 00:44:38.240
To any outside observer. it would appear as though...

784
00:44:38.240 --> 00:44:40.370
the object has stopped just outside the black hole.

785
00:44:40.870 --> 00:44:41.950
Last question.

786
00:44:41.950 --> 00:44:44.240
What do snakes. ducks. and possums all have in common?

787
00:44:45.540 --> 00:44:47.250
When hunted. they play dead.

788
00:44:49.370 --> 00:44:52.250
Ortegas. plot a course to take us close to the event horizon.

789
00:44:52.250 --> 00:44:54.500
Hemmer. you and the cadet have access to EV suits?

790
00:44:54.500 --> 00:44:56.960
HEMMER: <i>We do. sir. I hesitate to ask why.</i>

791
00:44:56.970 --> 00:44:59.260
You're going to slingshot off the black hole...

792
00:44:59.260 --> 00:45:02.260
and drop the AP 350 as a decoy?

793
00:45:06.060 --> 00:45:08.680
Captain. your plan requires flying the <i>Enterprise</i>...

794
00:45:08.690 --> 00:45:11.100
into one of the most turbulent phenomenons in space.

795
00:45:11.100 --> 00:45:13.020
Hull integrity is already compromised.

796
00:45:13.020 --> 00:45:14.500
That kind of force...
- She'll hold.

797
00:45:15.690 --> 00:45:17.280
The <i>Enterprise</i> is going to make it.

798
00:45:19.280 --> 00:45:20.280
She'll hold.

799
00:45:21.120 --> 00:45:22.370
We've got this.

800
00:45:22.740 --> 00:45:26.580
Erica. if anyone can surf a wave on a black hole. it's you.

801
00:45:26.580 --> 00:45:28.580
Ah. now you almost make it sound fun.

802
00:45:28.580 --> 00:45:30.210
Suit up. strap in.

803
00:45:30.630 --> 00:45:32.420
We're venting the hold on my signal.

804
00:45:35.550 --> 00:45:37.220
I commit you to the cosmos.

805
00:45:43.600 --> 00:45:46.560
I'm giving you high marks on your assessment today.

806
00:45:46.560 --> 00:45:48.310
You impressed me after all.

807
00:45:48.310 --> 00:45:49.890
Assuming that will still matter...

808
00:45:51.190 --> 00:45:52.310
thank you.

809
00:45:53.440 --> 00:45:56.280
Humans waste so much life worrying about death.

810
00:45:56.280 --> 00:45:59.860
The Aenar believe the end only comes once you have fulfilled your purpose.

811
00:45:59.860 --> 00:46:02.160
It provides meaning.
- I like that.

812
00:46:02.160 --> 00:46:03.830
So what was your purpose?

813
00:46:04.240 --> 00:46:05.830
To fix what is broken.

814
00:46:06.870 --> 00:46:08.410
You can throw in teaching.

815
00:46:08.410 --> 00:46:10.250
Maybe even being inspiring.

816
00:46:10.250 --> 00:46:11.380
A little.

817
00:46:11.790 --> 00:46:12.960
[LAUGHS]

818
00:46:13.840 --> 00:46:15.000
And you?

819
00:46:15.500 --> 00:46:17.630
What do you feel is the purpose of your life's path?

820
00:46:19.800 --> 00:46:21.340
I really don't know.

821
00:46:23.470 --> 00:46:25.180
Does that mean I'm not gonna die?

822
00:46:25.180 --> 00:46:26.770
There's only 1 way to find out.

823
00:46:33.690 --> 00:46:35.520
ZUNIGA: Inertial dampers at max.

824
00:46:35.520 --> 00:46:37.190
Brace for heavy gravity.

825
00:46:37.190 --> 00:46:38.780
ORTEGAS: We pull this off...

826
00:46:39.360 --> 00:46:41.450
it's officially the Pike Maneuver.

827
00:46:42.240 --> 00:46:43.990
Open a channel. Ship-wide.

828
00:46:46.240 --> 00:46:47.330
[COMMS CHIMING]

829
00:46:47.330 --> 00:46:49.370
Attention. this is the Captain speaking.

830
00:46:50.710 --> 00:46:54.170
Earlier today. we were reminded of the cost of exploration.

831
00:46:55.340 --> 00:46:57.380
<i>What it means to chart the stars...</i>

832
00:46:58.050 --> 00:47:01.430
<i>to push the boundaries of what is known and what is possible.</i>

833
00:47:03.640 --> 00:47:07.350
<i>When we seek out the unknown. we will find things that challenge us.</i>

834
00:47:08.850 --> 00:47:10.140
<i>That frighten us.</i>

835
00:47:12.060 --> 00:47:13.560
<i>But we do not back down.</i>

836
00:47:14.060 --> 00:47:16.400
We do not give in to fear.

837
00:47:18.190 --> 00:47:20.740
And I believe today will not be our last mission...

838
00:47:21.820 --> 00:47:23.370
but our finest hour.

839
00:47:24.530 --> 00:47:26.240
All hands make ready for impact.

840
00:47:48.810 --> 00:47:50.560
Gorn ship changing course.

841
00:47:50.560 --> 00:47:52.100
Accretion disc in sight.

842
00:47:54.810 --> 00:47:55.810
Hit it.

843
00:47:59.530 --> 00:48:01.860
[SHIP GROANING. RATTLING]

844
00:48:12.460 --> 00:48:14.080
Vent the hold!

845
00:48:18.000 --> 00:48:20.510
[BOTH EXCLAIMING. GRUNTING]

846
00:48:42.860 --> 00:48:44.120
Ortegas.

847
00:48:45.660 --> 00:48:47.660
[ENGINES WHIRRING UP]

848
00:49:21.940 --> 00:49:23.610
[POWERING UP]

849
00:49:24.860 --> 00:49:26.160
Report.

850
00:49:26.160 --> 00:49:27.620
No sign of the Gorn.

851
00:49:28.080 --> 00:49:30.040
They've gone. sir. We did it.

852
00:49:31.540 --> 00:49:32.960
Show me Main Cargo Bay.

853
00:49:44.380 --> 00:49:45.930
Pike to Main Cargo Bay.

854
00:49:49.600 --> 00:49:50.890
Hemmer.

855
00:49:50.890 --> 00:49:53.060
Hemmer? Uhura?

856
00:49:54.060 --> 00:49:55.400
Report.

857
00:50:07.830 --> 00:50:10.990
La'An. Send a recovery team.

858
00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:13.250
UHURA: <i>We're here. sir. We're still here.</i>

859
00:50:13.250 --> 00:50:14.420
[SIGHS]

860
00:50:16.880 --> 00:50:17.880
[SIGHS]

861
00:50:30.260 --> 00:50:31.430
[PIKE SIGHS]

862
00:50:33.560 --> 00:50:35.140
Well. I don't know about you...

863
00:50:37.270 --> 00:50:38.440
but...

864
00:50:39.480 --> 00:50:41.610
I think that was quite a miracle.

865
00:50:43.110 --> 00:50:44.700
What about next time?

866
00:50:46.070 --> 00:50:48.200
The Gorn have never come this far before.

867
00:50:49.330 --> 00:50:51.450
They're opening up new hunting grounds.

868
00:50:52.750 --> 00:50:54.160
Next time.

869
00:50:55.790 --> 00:50:58.000
Next time. they...

870
00:50:58.960 --> 00:51:00.710
They won't catch us by surprise.

871
00:51:05.380 --> 00:51:06.970
We'll be ready for 'em.

872
00:52:05.820 --> 00:52:09.740
LA'AN: <i>Personal Log. Stardate 3177.9.</i>

873
00:52:11.370 --> 00:52:14.120
<i>Today. the</i> Enterprise <i>encountered the Gorn.</i>

874
00:52:16.460 --> 00:52:18.130
<i>7 of the crew...</i>

875
00:52:19.040 --> 00:52:20.590
<i>gave their lives.</i>

876
00:52:31.060 --> 00:52:32.560
<i>But...</i>

877
00:52:34.850 --> 00:52:36.390
<i>we survived.</i>

878
00:52:40.680 --> 00:53:51.920
%$%$

879
00:52:43.680 --> 00:53:51.920
STAR TREK

880
00:52:43.680 --> 00:53:51.920
STRANGE NEW WORLDS
